This  project  is  a  simple  implementation  of  a  neurale  network  tranning
algorithm.  For starting  it will use the  sigmoide  activation  function. This
project uses a dependency lib called libmatrix for the operations on matrices.

----- DEPENDENCYS -----

  libmatrix.a :
    You need to clone a git repository, get the libmatrix.a and libmatrix.h
    files and put them in the right directory.

    Clone the repository and generate the needed files :
      git clone https://github.com/LaTaupeEspagnole/matrix-prod-bench.git
      cd matrix-prod-bench
      make lib

    Then copy the file 'matrix-prod-bench/libmatrix.a' in the root of this
    project and the file 'matrix-prod-bench/includes/libmatrix.h' into the
    includes directory of this project.


----- BUILD -----

  Build the project :
    make              -> builds the project in release mode (-O3).
    make debug        -> builds the project in debug mode (-g).

    make clean        -> clean all the files generated by the makefile.
    make clean-deps   -> clean the libmatrix files.
    make clean-all    -> same as 'make clean clean-deps'.


----- USE -----

  ./main          -> starts the program.
  (Section to complet)


